You can open an existing document in order to Tidy it by following these simple
simple steps, below.

1. Use the **Open…** menu item in the **File** menu. ![all-menu-file][all-menu-file]{: .menu_dropshadow}


2. Or, Drag a file in Finder to <%= pne %>’s icon in the Dock. ![dock icon][icon_32x32]

<% if target_feature?(:feature_supports_applescript) %>
3. Or, [Create an AppleScript program][applescript] to tell Finder to open a file with
   <%= pne %>.
<% end %>

If you are using <%= mac_os %> 10.12 or newer, then documents may
open in a new window, or in a new tab in an existing window. This depends on
settings in **System Preferences**. See [Using Tabbed Windows][docu-tabbed] in
the **Reference** section.
{: .note}
